From 653eab62d7844f86968e8a83c3f27f79b2254885 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Jan 2026 18:14:51 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Fix unicast client FSM race condition causing UNCALIBRATED
 state

Problem:

Boundary Clock (BC) upstream ports remained stuck in UNCALIBRATED state when
connecting to unicast grandmasters. The port would successfully receive ANNOUNCE
messages and complete BMCA master selection, but never request SYNC/DELAY_RESP
services, preventing transition to SLAVE state.

Root Cause:

The unicast client finite state machine (FSM) has a race condition in its
initialization sequence:

1. At startup, unicast master table entries are created with IP addresses but
   unknown port identities (initialized to 0xFF...FF)

2. Client sends REQUEST_UNICAST_TRANSMISSION for ANNOUNCE messages

3. When GRANT_UNICAST_TRANSMISSION arrives, unicast_client_grant() transitions
   FSM from UC_WAIT -> UC_HAVE_ANN and learns the master's port identity from
   the ANNOUNCE message header

4. BMCA runs and selects the best master, calling handle_state_decision_event()
   in clock.c

5. handle_state_decision_event() should notify unicast clients via
   unicast_client_state_changed() when a new parent is selected

6. unicast_client_state_changed() sends UC_EV_SELECTED event to matching master,
   transitioning FSM from UC_HAVE_ANN -> UC_NEED_SYDY

7. UC_NEED_SYDY state triggers REQUEST_UNICAST_TRANSMISSION for SYNC/DELAY_RESP

The race occurs because step 5 was missing; handle_state_decision_event() never
called unicast_client_state_changed() when selecting a new parent. Additionally,
even if it had been called, it would have been called BEFORE the port identity
was learned in step 3, causing the port identity comparison to fail.

Solution:

This commit implements a two-part fix:

Part 1: Notify on parent selection (clock.c)

Add unicast_client_state_changed() call in handle_state_decision_event() when
a new best master is selected (fresh_best == true). This ensures all ports are
notified when BMCA selects a new parent.

Part 2: Trigger on identity learning (unicast_client.c)

In unicast_client_grant(), when receiving the first ANNOUNCE grant and learning
the master's port identity, immediately call unicast_client_state_changed() if
the identity was previously unknown. This handles the case where BMCA has already
selected this master as parent, but the identity match couldn't occur because
the identity wasn't known yet.

The combination ensures the FSM progresses regardless of timing:
- If BMCA runs before identity is learned: Part 2 triggers state change
- If BMCA runs after identity is learned: Part 1 triggers state change
- If BMCA runs during identity learning: Both parts are idempotent

Technical Details

The unicast client FSM states:
- UC_WAIT: Initial state, requesting ANNOUNCE
- UC_HAVE_ANN: ANNOUNCE granted, waiting for parent selection
- UC_NEED_SYDY: Parent selected, requesting SYNC/DELAY_RESP
- UC_HAVE_SYDY: All services granted, operational

The fix ensures the UC_HAVE_ANN -> UC_NEED_SYDY transition occurs by sending
UC_EV_SELECTED event at the correct time, regardless of the race between:
1. Learning port identity from ANNOUNCE grant
2. BMCA selecting that master as parent

Test plan:
Verified with BC connecting to two unicast GMs:
- Port successfully transitions UC_WAIT -> UC_HAVE_ANN -> UC_NEED_SYDY -> UC_HAVE_SYDY
- SYNC and DELAY_RESP messages received
- Port transitions LISTENING -> UNCALIBRATED -> SLAVE
- Time synchronization operational

Signed-off-by: Cole Walker <cole.walker@windriver.com>
---
 clock.c          | 8 ++++++++
 unicast_client.c | 6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/clock.c b/clock.c
index 2f5c9bf..bea3ef1 100644
--- a/clock.c
+++ b/clock.c
@@ -43,6 +43,7 @@
 #include "tlv.h"
 #include "tsproc.h"
 #include "uds.h"
+#include "unicast_client.h"
 #include "util.h"
 
 #define N_CLOCK_PFD (N_POLLFD + 1) /* one extra per port, for the fault timer */
@@ -1939,6 +1940,13 @@ static void handle_state_decision_event(struct clock *c)
 	c->best = best;
 	c->best_id = best_id;
 
+	/* Notify unicast clients if parent changed */
+	if (fresh_best) {
+		LIST_FOREACH(piter, &c->ports, list) {
+			unicast_client_state_changed(piter);
+		}
+	}
+
 	LIST_FOREACH(piter, &c->ports, list) {
 		enum port_state ps;
 		enum fsm_event event;
diff --git a/unicast_client.c b/unicast_client.c
index e71307f..2f8640f 100644
--- a/unicast_client.c
+++ b/unicast_client.c
@@ -452,9 +452,15 @@ void unicast_client_grant(struct port *p, struct ptp_message *m,
 	switch (ucma->state) {
 	case UC_WAIT:
 		if (mtype == ANNOUNCE) {
+			int was_unknown;
+			was_unknown = ucma->portIdentity.portNumber == 0xFFFF;
 			ucma->state = unicast_fsm(ucma->state, UC_EV_GRANT_ANN);
 			ucma->portIdentity = m->header.sourcePortIdentity;
 			unicast_client_set_renewal(p, ucma, g->durationField);
+			/* Trigger state change now that we have port identity */
+			if (was_unknown) {
+				unicast_client_state_changed(p);
+			}
 		}
 		break;
 	case UC_HAVE_ANN:
